reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Doesn’t work and broke my current setup
reviews.reviewText: I used the 1080 slim model with 2 eufy cam 2 pro. I liked it so much I decided to upgrade the camera of the doorbell from 1080p to this 2k.That was a huge mistake. When I paired this doorbell, I wouldn’t get any notifications (except when they pressed ring button) of any motion. My other cameras continued to work fine. I contacted eufy support and got some terrible support. They told me the chime can only support 1 camera. I explained to them I previously had 3 cameras on it and it worked fine. They kept saying only one camera and I’ll have to buy a homebase. I checked on eufy support and found documentation stating the chime supported 3 cameras. This was directly on their website. They said that isn’t supported anymore. I also found similar documents stating it would support 2 cameras per chime. He said that also wasn’t true. Again, this was on the official eufy website. He said he updated my account and I would need to reset my cameras for it to take affect. I thought he did something to help the new camera work. He didn’t. He actually ruined my other three cameras. When they came back on, they no longer worked. They won’t send notifications and often unpair themself from chime. When I told him that he said he had to push the new feature set which would limit me to only 1 camera per chime and it would work better. I was pretty frustrated and asked him to revert that as I used 3 cameras and they worked fine for many months. He wasn’t interested. He told me to buy a new homebase and get over using the chrome again. I told him I wasn’t paying them more money since they just ruined my product set up. He stated I can earn a free home base by “donating videos”. I did and found you only get enough credit for half. Then you can’t do anything with the credits and there’s no way to earn more. It’s appears to be a scam. You can’t earn enough points to ever redeem anything. I have spoke to many people and it’s clear they added a feature to limit my chime to only allow one camera. Forcing me to buy a new product from them that I didn’t actually need.I will be returning all of my eufy products that I can and recycling the rest and will never give maker or eufy another dollar. They’re a very predatory company.Also, probably should have mentioned this sooner before going off subject but it appears I got a used, defective device that was missing pieces and doesn’t function correctly. If I received a working product from Amazon, eufy tech support wouldn’t have been able to add this new “feature”.Either way. I wouldn’t recommend any of their products.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great gear, attachment hardware wasn't so good.
reviews.reviewText: I loved the local only nature of the eufy system. I'm not a fan of cloud based systems at all. The only problem I had was with the screws shipped with the device- I stripped three of them while using my drill/driver on the lowest torque setting, and without even pushing the trigger hard. A couple of bucks for a bag of screws at Home Depot made installation a breeze.

reviews.reviewTitle: Impressive camera quality and Motion detection. Great battery life (depending on your settings)
reviews.reviewText: Great camera quality! The wireless doorbell captures clear images and videos, providing a reliable security feature for my home. The battery life is impressive, lasting for an extended period before needing a recharge. The installation process was straightforward, and the wireless connectivity ensures a hassle-free setup. Overall, a fantastic addition to my home security system.

I got this Eufy Security Video Doorbell 2K HD that really works now. Previously, I got a Eufy Security Video Doorbell with the Homebase. The later video doorbell did not work well since there were tons of misses than hits. It did not capture videos of people passing by my front door where the doorbell video camera was installed. If it did capture videos of people, the video plays people that have already passed by without recognizing their faces. I became frustrated with the Eufy Security Doorbell with the Homebase so I returned the Eufy Doorobell with the Homebase to Amazon. I scouted out for another doorbell video camera but I am unsure about their quality and how good their customer service is. I realize that Eufy security has good customer service rating so I settled for another Eufy security doorbell thinking that the first Eufy video doorbell could just be defective, or not working as it should be. I was able to find the Eufy security video doorbell 2K HD that is a little bit cheaper than the first one. As to its performance, having observed it for a week, I can say that it is doing its job as described in the advertisement. I am satisfied with the quality so far, and I cannot complain this time. However, I have to see its performance for a month to be certain how good its quality, and performance.

We had a ring wireless before and not only did it not have internal memory, but the longer we had it (4 months) the more useless it became. Features started to not work one by one until one of our phones could no longer connect. This one is hassle free. Easy to install, set up and use. Again, unlike the ring. Sometimes it takes a bit longer to connect when you're away from home, but it's not that big of a deal.

reviews.reviewTitle: Works really really well and no monthly fees.
reviews.reviewText: I like this doorbell compared to other doorbells I have purchased. This works really well, night vision is great, motion detector works really well and picture quality is excellent. Most of all everything is saved on my local hard drive and I have privacy to my videos and pictures. I would recommend this product to anyone.

Difficult to configure alerts if you don't want an alarm on your phone every time you neighbours walk by. Motion detection masking doesn't work well. Ads every time you open the app.Once you work around these problems it's a pretty good doorbell.
